</tr><tr><td colspan="2"><font>The Index of  			 Independence in Activities of Daily Living is based on an evaluation of the  			 functional independence or dependence of patients in bathing, dressing, going  			 to the toilet, transferring, continence, and feeding. Specific definitions of  			 functional independence and dependence appear below the index.</font><br /><ol type="A"><li><font>Independent in feeding, continence,  				  transferring, going to the toilet, dressing, and bathing.</font></li>
<li><font>Independent in all but one of these  				  functions.</font></li>
<li><font>Independent in all but bathing and one  				  additional function.</font></li>
<li><font>Independent in all but bathing, dressing, and  				  one additional function.</font></li>
<li><font>Independent in all but bathing, dressing, going  				  to the toilet, and one additional function.</font></li>
<li><font>Independent in all but bathing, dressing, going  				  to the toilet, transferring, and one additional function.</font></li>
<li><font>Dependent in all six functions.</font></li>
</ol><p><font>Other Dependent in at least two functions, but  			 not classifiable as C, D, E, or F.Independence means without  			 supervision, direction, or active personal assistance, except as specifically  			 noted below. This is based on actual status and not on ability. A patient who  			 refuses to perform a function is considered as not performing the function,  			 even though he is deemed able.</font></p>
</td>
</tr><tr><td><font><b>BATHING</b> (Sponge, shower or tub)Independent: assistance  			 only in bathing a single part (as back or disabled extremity) or bathes self  			 completely.Dependent: assistance in bathing more than one part of the  			 body; assistance in getting in or out of tub or does not bathe  			 self.</font></td>
<td><font><b>TRANSFER</b>Independent: moves in and out of bed independently  			 and moves in and out of chair independently (may or may not be using mechanical  			 supports). Dependent: assistance in moving in or out of bed and/or  			 chair; does not perform one or more transfers.</font></td>
</tr><tr><td><font><b>DRESSING</b>Independent: gets clothes from closets and  			 drawers, puts on clothes, outer garments, braces; manages fasteners; act of  			 tying shoes is excluded. Dependent: does not dress self or remains  			 partly undressed.</font></td>
<td><font><b>CONTINENCE</b>Independent: urination and defecation entirely  			 self-controlled. Dependent: partial or total maintenance in urination  			 or defecation; partial or total control by enemas, catheters, or regulated use  			 of urinals and/or bedpans.</font></td>
</tr><tr><td><font><b>GOING TO  			 TOILET</b>Independent: gets to toilets, gets on and off toilets, arranges  			 clothes, cleans organs of excretion, (may manage own bedpan used at night only  			 and may or may not be using mechanical supports).Dependent: uses bedpan  			 or commode or receives assistance in getting to and using toilet.</font></td>
<td><font><b>FEEDING</b>Independent: gets food from plate or its equivalent  			 into mouth; (precutting of meat and preparation of food, as buttering bread are  			 excluded from evaluation).Dependent: assistance in act of feeding (see  			 above); does not eat at all or parenteral feeding.</font></td>
</tr></table><table title="EXHIBIT III.1. SAAF ADL Battery"><tr><td colspan="2"><b><font>EXHIBIT III.1. (<i>continued</i>)SAAF ADL  			 Battery</font></b></td>
</tr><tr><td colspan="2"><font><b>DIRECTIONS</b>Ask each "Do you?" question.If the  			 applicant is "Intact," skip questions as indicated.If the applicant  			 answers "Helper" or "Does not do," then ask the "could you...if you had to  			 now?" Use the "could you" codes to code the applicant's response. For  			 all mentally retarded applicants, ask all questions (do not skip) in order to  			 identify any specific problems or needs for help.</font></td>
</tr><tr><td><font><b>16.Do you walk up and down a flight of  			 stairs?</b>(1)Intact -- Able to go up and down at  			 least one flight of stairs safely without using any type of  			 support.(2)Limited -- Able to go up and down at least one  			 flight of stairs with the use of side support or handrail or by using a cane or  			 portable supports which must be managed without  			 assistance.(3)Helper -- Able to go up and down at least  			 one flight of stairs but needs assistance or supervision for  			 safety.(4)Does not do.(9)Not asked  			 / not answered / don't know IF "INTACT" SKIP TO QUESTION 19</font></td>
<td><font>Do you?  			 _____Could you?  			 _____(1)Yes(2)No(0)Inappropriate(9)Not  			 asked / Not answered / Don't know</font></td>
</tr><tr><td><font><b>17.Do you walk a distance of 50 yards on level  			 ground without help of any kind?</b>(1)Intact -- Able  			 to walk at least 50 yards without use of aids.(2)Limited  			 -- Able to walk 50 yards by uses a brace or prosthesis on leg; or uses a cane,  			 crutches, walkerette, or special shoes; no assistance, supervision for safety  			 or guarding is needed.(3)Helper -- Able to walk at least  			 50 yards with a person to assist or supervise for  			 safety.(4)Does not do.(9)Not asked  			 / not answered / don't know(0)Inappropriate, coded intact  			 on Q. 16.</font></td>
<td><font>Do you?  			 _____Could you?  			 _____(1)Yes(2)No(0)Inappropriate(9)Not  			 asked / Not answered / Don't know</font></td>
</tr><tr><td colspan="2"><font><b>OF  			 WHEELCHAIR PEOPLE ONLY</b></font></td>
</tr><tr><td><font><b>18.Do you travel a distance of 50 yards, go  			 around corners in your wheelchair without someone pushing you?</b>  			 (1)Intact -- Able to propel wheelchair independently  			 for at least 50 yards; able to go around corners, turn around, maneuver the  			 chair to a table, bed, toilet, etc.; able to negotiate up to a 3 grade,  			 maneuver on rugs; over doorsills, etc.(2)Limited -- As  			 above but requires a powered wheelchair or takes more than a reasonable  			 time.(3)Helper -- Needs assistance of a person in  			 propelling or maneuvering wheelchair.(4)Does not  			 do.(9)Not asked / not answered / don't  			 know(0)Inappropriate, applicant not in  			 wheelchair.</font></td>
<td><font>Do you?  			 _____Could you?  			 _____(1)Yes(2)No(0)Inappropriate(9)Not  			 asked / Not answered / Don't know</font></td>
</tr><tr><td><font><b>19.Do you get in and out of the bath or shower  			 without assistance?</b>(1)Intact -- Able to enter and  			 leave a tub or shower safely.(2)Limited -- As above but  			 requires adaptive or assistive devices such as grab bars or special seat or a  			 lift, or takes more than a reasonable amount of time but not  			 assistance.(3)Helper(4)Does not  			 do.(9)Not asked / not answered / don't knowIF  			 "INTACT" SKIP TO QUESTION 21</font></td>
